---
import WarningCallout from './WarningCallout.astro';
---

<div class="space-y-10">
  <!-- Variant 1 (canonical): location constraint -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">
      Location constraint (canonical)
    </h3>
    <p
      class="t-body mt-2"
      style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px; max-width: 70ch;"
    >
      The default <code>Important</code> label. A 1px amber warning frame
      carries the prominence (a full frame, never a colour stripe or fill).
      Body text stays Ink.
    </p>
    <div
      class="mt-3 px-6 py-6"
      style="border: 1px solid var(--color-rule); background: var(--color-bg);"
    >
      <WarningCallout>
        You must be physically located within NSW at the time of online
        training. The course cannot be completed if you are interstate on the
        day of your session.
      </WarningCallout>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Variant 2 (custom label): eligibility constraint with a link -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">
      Custom label, eligibility constraint
    </h3>
    <p
      class="t-body mt-2"
      style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px; max-width: 70ch;"
    >
      The <code>label</code> prop reframes the callout, here as
      <code>Eligibility</code>. The body slot carries an inline link.
    </p>
    <div
      class="mt-3 px-6 py-6"
      style="border: 1px solid var(--color-rule); background: var(--color-bg);"
    >
      <WarningCallout label="Eligibility">
        An Owner Builder permit is required once the value of work crosses
        your state's threshold. Confirm the current figure with
        <a
          href="https://www.nsw.gov.au/housing-and-construction"
          class="link-dotted"
          rel="external"
        >
          Building Commission NSW</a>
        before you enrol.
      </WarningCallout>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
